  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed antennas, transmission dishes and supporting structures, by reason of their inappropriate siting, height, scale and appearance, would be dominant and discordant additions to the roof of the building and would causing clear visual harm to the character and appearance of the Priory Green Conservation Area and the Grade A Locally Listed building, whilst also resulting in harm to the protected LV7 view. The proposal is therefore contrary to policies D1, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policies PLAN1, DH1, DH2 and ST3 of Islington's Strategic and Development Management Policies (2023), the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide (2017), Priory Green Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2003) & The NPPF 2023."
